    "If nothing was provable, then, at least it all became instantly suspect; I felt myself going closer to - to certainty as to not only what mattered and what did not, but also who my enemies truly were.\nAnd so in hindsight this gradually became my theme for that General Mumbing of Reminder Arks; I would hitch up the historical train and allow other expressions to ride upon it. I rescued the stone sculpture of Glyptapredescribingur face from a rubbish dump (with a little false authority I claimed for myself before officiating civil servants), and it formed the head of a History Ark to traverse the wetlands at dawn of clearing. Elsewhere loaned especially created eccentrically bristling metal abstract sculpture of three flames breathing deeply rode on the train.\n",
