    "Sing, sing, sing a senseless song. Where had her father gone? Best thing he could have done for his kid; shitbuster had been like taking a drunk's son to church.\nGreg Masters splices, and swirls develop in the floating strata of colored vinyl, silver-gray pools of hanging wrinkles. Who dressed her up, Daddy with his nose against her back or did Mommy do it? The image, poignant and vague on the blue wall beyond the stereo, never mirrors itself clearly in photos or eyes because at that instant of recognition or recollection when it awaits notice, arrest, it so sharply differs from what it is at this hour as to disappear. Moving too quickly in seeming to move too slowly, it becomes invisible. Love's invisible triumph. Becoming invisible oneself.\n",
